## 3. Component Tree Patterns

**This section is the API the ux-consultant and feature implementer cite by subsection number.** Each subsection names an established shape, gives a canonical code block, lists reference files, and includes a DON'T anti-pattern. When a feature spans any of these subsections, the authoring agent MUST cite the subsection and match the shape.

Missing a subsection a feature needs? That is a doc gap — flag it in the run, do not invent.

### 3.1 Dashboard Tabs

A `*Tab.tsx` (or equivalent) that renders a filterable, paginated table inside a dashboard page.

**Canonical shape:**

{{TAB_SHELL_CANONICAL}}

<!-- Example (shadcn + Tailwind):
```tsx
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <div className="flex justify-between gap-4">
      <div>
        <CardTitle>{t("...title")}</CardTitle>
        <CardDescription>{t("...desc")}</CardDescription>
      </div>
      {/* toolbar / bulk actions */}
    </div>
    {/* filter inputs */}
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <DataTable columns={columns} data={data} ... />
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```
-->

**Rules:**
- {{TAB_SHELL_RULES}}

<!-- Example bullets:
- A `*Tab.tsx` that renders a `DataTable` MUST wrap it in the shell primitive named above.
- Filters belong inside the header region, not above the shell.
- A toolbar (bulk-action buttons, status badge) appears in the header only when selection state > 0.
-->

**Reference files** (mimic these — do not invent a new shape):
{{TAB_SHELL_REFERENCES}}

**DON'T:**

{{TAB_SHELL_ANTIPATTERN}}

