### 3.2 Row Actions

Action buttons rendered inside a data-table row (view, edit, claim, download, reject, …).

**Canonical shape:**

{{ROW_ACTIONS_CANONICAL}}

<!-- Example (shadcn-style helper):
```tsx
import { createActionsColumn, viewAction, downloadAction } from "@/components/ui/data-table";

createActionsColumn<RowT>(deps, {
  headerKey: "common.actions",
  actions: [
    viewAction({ tooltipKey: "common.view", onClick: onView }),
    downloadAction({ tooltipKey: "common.download", onClick: onDownload }),
  ],
});
```
-->

**Rules:**
- {{ROW_ACTIONS_RULES}}

<!-- Example bullets:
- Every row-action cell MUST use the shared helper named above. Do not hand-roll inline buttons.
- Use the helper's existing action factories (viewAction, downloadAction, etc.) before inventing a new one.
- Row actions are **icon buttons with tooltips**, not text links.
- New action types must be added as factories to the helper, not inline in feature columns.
-->

**Reference files**:
{{ROW_ACTIONS_REFERENCES}}

**DON'T:**

{{ROW_ACTIONS_ANTIPATTERN}}

<!-- Example:
```tsx
// WRONG — hand-rolled text link; bypasses the helper, no tooltip, no a11y label
<button className="text-primary hover:underline" onClick={...}>
  {t("common.view")}
</button>
```
-->

